text: Katherine Nataly Arias Peña (born 2 April 1986) is a Colombian international footballer who currently plays as a center back. She represented Colombia at the 2011 FIFA Women's World Cup in Germany, 2012 Summer Olympics in London and 2015 FIFA Women's World Cup in Canada as well as the 2016 Summer Olympics in Brazil. ==References== == External links == * Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:Colombian women's footballers Category:Olympic footballers of Colombia Category:Footballers at the 2012 Summer Olympics Category:Footballers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:2011 FIFA Women's World Cup players Category:2015 FIFA Women's World Cup players Category:Women's association football defenders Category:Colombia women's international footballers Category:Colombian footballers Category:Maryland Terrapins women's soccer players Category:Sportspeople from Arlington County, Virginia Category:Soccer players from Virginia Category:American women's soccer players Category:Footballers at the 2015 Pan American Games Category:American people of Colombian descent Category:American people of Venezuelan descent Category:Naturalized citizens of Colombia Category:Atlanta Silverbacks Women players
